The paper deals with compressed sensing based unsourced random-access communication, which involves encoding messages into sparse binary vectors and compressing them using random linear mappings. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Coding Theory (cs.CC) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of spatial coupling and the analysis of the asymptotic infinite blocklength limit, which are common in the sub-categories of Multimedia (cs.MM), Signal Processing (cs.SI), and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI).
